Kitchen and Dining Room Furniture

From holiday gatherings to lively dinner parties, some of our most treasured memories happen in the kitchen or around the dining table. Bring comfort and style to these occasions with the right furniture.


Kitchen and Dining Room Furniture Styles

Kitchen and dining room tables should be inviting for simple meals and large gatherings alike. Look for dining room sets that offer easy adjustments in table length and comfortable chairs. Here are some trends to consider:

  • Industrial Elegance: Metal dining room sets provide a slim look, perfect for small or minimalist spaces. Sets that feature reclaimed or distressed wood fit well in homes with modern or industrial decor.
  • Versatile Black: Black dining room sets are versatile. Pair them with stark gray and white decor for a contemporary look, or add rich colors for a warmer space.
  • Rustic vs. Formal: Alder, birch, and lighter oak finishes convey a more rustic vibe, while walnut, cherry, or darker oak colors are ideal for more formal settings.
  • Casual and Compact: For a casual look, choose a round table and chairs set in easy-to-clean wood or laminate. Kitchen and dining tables with bench seating make stylish use of informal, smaller spaces.
  • Eclectic: Mix and match your kitchen and dining chairs for an eclectic look. Choose patterned dining chair sets with straight arms for the head and foot of the table. For the side chairs, go with solid-colored, armless versions.


Unique Pieces to Fit Your Space

You can create an inviting atmosphere with stylish kitchen chairs and bar stools with high backs and plush upholstered seating. Complete your dining room with a sideboard or buffet table, as well as a wine rack, for added storage and style. For special occasions, a folding table can help accommodate several extra guests or act as a serving table.


Make your kitchen and dining room furniture multifunctional. Kitchen islands and utility carts give you storage and room for meal prep, but they also work for extra countertop or rolling surface space when you're entertaining.


For kitchens without a pantry or ones that need more shelf space, check out pantry cabinets and baker's racks. If you've got heirloom dishes to show off, a display cabinet can organize it all in a way that leaves the fine china and silverware accessible. Curio cabinets also bring your beloved collectibles into a room where the whole family can admire them.


A cozy home has a welcoming and functional kitchen or dining table. Find the right set, then add other dining room furniture to finish out the room right. Shop online or on our mobile app for the furniture you'll love to see every day. We'll ship it right to your doorstep.
